│ which represents the range {255, 0, 1} (wrapping range). This range has size 3, and ReachableCaseCount is also 3 (cases 0, 1, 2 are considered reachable). The condition `!CR.isSizeLargerThan(3)` evaluates   │
│ to true because CR.size() == 3, leading the pass to incorrectly conclude that all possible values are covered by the cases. However, the actual value -1 (255) is not covered by any case (cases are 0, 1, 2), │
│ so the default destination should remain reachable.\n\nThe issue is that the pass assumes that if the constant range size equals the number of reachable cases, then all values in the range are covered by    │
